<section id="fs-id1170572347374" class="section-exercises">
<para id="fs-id1170572347378">For the following exercises, consider the function <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>|</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>|</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<exercise id="fs-id1170571655731">
<problem id="fs-id1170571655733">
<para id="fs-id1170571655735"><emphasis effect="bold">[T]</emphasis> Complete the following table for the function. Round your solutions to four decimal places.</para>
